00:02:55.260 --> 00:02:59.640
We're moving away from this
focus on specific platforms,

00:02:59.640 --> 00:03:03.740
specific products, and trying
to think about the world the way

00:03:03.740 --> 00:03:05.050
you see it.

00:03:05.050 --> 00:03:07.590
And the way you tend to
see it is you see Google

00:03:07.590 --> 00:03:10.000
as one company, one service.

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:12.550
You don't really care
about our org chart.

00:03:12.550 --> 00:03:15.190
You want to think about,
I want to use some service

00:03:15.190 --> 00:03:17.700
from Google, and just
be able to just use it.

00:03:17.700 --> 00:03:19.580
You don't want to get
told, oh, I'm sorry,

00:03:19.580 --> 00:03:21.422
that's not my department.

00:03:21.422 --> 00:03:23.130
You don't want to be
told, oh, I'm sorry,

00:03:23.130 --> 00:03:24.720
that's not managed over here.

00:03:24.720 --> 00:03:27.305
Please talk to the person in the
right department in New York.

00:03:27.305 --> 00:03:28.430
