00:16:55.120 --> 00:16:56.610
I've learned to ignore it.

00:16:56.610 --> 00:16:59.000
That's because I'm a bad person.

00:16:59.000 --> 00:17:00.902
However, I am not alone.

00:17:00.902 --> 00:17:02.610
There are many bad
people on this planet.

00:17:02.610 --> 00:17:04.390
There's about 7 billion of us.

00:17:04.390 --> 00:17:06.854
And we've learned that
these emails telling

00:17:06.854 --> 00:17:08.729
you to come back, these
notifications telling

00:17:08.729 --> 00:17:11.429
us to come back, it's a machine
somewhere telling you you

00:17:11.429 --> 00:17:12.970
should probably play
this game again.

00:17:12.970 --> 00:17:14.595
It doesn't have any
meaning, it doesn't

00:17:14.595 --> 00:17:16.180
have any emotional weight.

00:17:16.180 --> 00:17:18.400
What does have emotional
weight is getting

00:17:18.400 --> 00:17:22.250
a message from somebody you
know telling you something

00:17:22.250 --> 00:17:24.710
has happened, something
worthwhile is going on.

00:17:24.710 --> 00:17:29.000
So for example, here's a recipe
I shared on Google+ for honey

00:17:29.000 --> 00:17:30.270
soy chicken.

00:17:30.270 --> 00:17:32.000
Of course, I can't
cook because I

00:17:32.000 --> 00:17:34.790
worked at Google for
nearly seven years.

00:17:34.790 --> 00:17:37.350
So I make a post saying,
if only I could cook.

00:17:37.350 --> 00:17:39.440
And hopefully, somebody I
know will click on that,

00:17:39.440 --> 00:17:42.040
learn the recipe, and
then invite me around

00:17:42.040 --> 00:17:46.400
because they made
this-- it could happen.

