By the way, who here has
heard the acoustic version

00:17:50.640 --> 00:17:53.220
of Justin Bieber's "Boyfriend"?

00:17:53.220 --> 00:17:55.554
It's actually pretty good.

00:17:55.554 --> 00:17:57.470
I can say that because
this is all on the NDA.

00:18:00.150 --> 00:18:03.450
But hey, I can share that song
and people can click on it

00:18:03.450 --> 00:18:05.130
and they can listen to the song.

00:18:05.130 --> 00:18:10.040
But the point is, I share this,
and people say, what the hell?

00:18:10.040 --> 00:18:13.670
And they click on it,
because why would I say this?

00:18:13.670 --> 00:18:16.571
And then they say, actually,
it's not that horrible.

00:18:16.571 --> 00:18:18.570
And then they show it to
a few of their friends.

00:18:18.570 --> 00:18:21.280
It's not that horrible,
the acoustic version.

00:18:21.280 --> 00:18:22.910
And it spreads it that way.

00:18:22.910 --> 00:18:25.250
This is how things like
Flappy Bird spreads.

00:18:25.250 --> 00:18:27.500
And it's that
message that spreads.

00:18:27.500 --> 00:18:30.260
It's the idea of somebody
actually saying this.

00:18:30.260 --> 00:18:34.390
By the way, in this version,
this app, Soundwave, actually

00:18:34.390 --> 00:18:35.900
created that message for me.

00:18:35.900 --> 00:18:38.940
I had the option of whether I
wanted to edit or delete this.

00:18:38.940 --> 00:18:40.830
I would never say,
"check out" this song.

00:18:40.830 --> 00:18:43.710
I would say, "hey, give
this song a listen."

00:18:43.710 --> 00:18:47.840
Point is, when you share what
we call an interactive post,

00:18:47.840 --> 00:18:49.690
you get the call to
action button, which

00:18:49.690 --> 00:18:53.700
says Listen here, Learn here.

00:18:53.700 --> 00:18:54.955
You get a pre-field of text.

00:18:54.955 --> 00:18:58.020
You can +Mention up to
10 of the user's friends.

00:18:58.020 --> 00:19:01.300
So that's a notification the
user will see across any Google

00:19:01.300 --> 00:19:04.610
product across all
of their devices.

00:19:04.610 --> 00:19:07.600
But because it's a
human-mediated message,

00:19:07.600 --> 00:19:12.410
they know it came from a person
and that person was involved.

00:19:12.410 --> 00:19:14.840
For example, this is
an app called Fancy,

00:19:14.840 --> 00:19:17.050
and they have a really
nice affiliate scheme

00:19:17.050 --> 00:19:19.370
where you buy stuff from them.

00:19:19.370 --> 00:19:22.880
It's a business model
where you give them money

00:19:22.880 --> 00:19:24.700
and they give you stuff.

00:19:24.700 --> 00:19:26.620
It's a Web 3.0 business model.

00:19:29.350 --> 00:19:35.690
In this case, I'm sharing a
vintage Rolex Submariner watch.

00:19:35.690 --> 00:19:37.400
It's ridiculously expensive.

00:19:37.400 --> 00:19:40.110
As you can see, I've
hidden the amount of zeroes

00:19:40.110 --> 00:19:41.760
because it goes off the edge.

00:19:41.760 --> 00:19:43.780
It's like $30,000 for a watch.

00:19:43.780 --> 00:19:45.870
But it's a really nice
watch, apparently.

00:19:45.870 --> 00:19:47.740
So I share this to my stream.

00:19:47.740 --> 00:19:51.767
And say Larry or Sergey was
following me and they saw this,

00:19:51.767 --> 00:19:53.600
and they go, oh, that's
nice, and they click

00:19:53.600 --> 00:20:01.430
Buy-- they would be
taken into the Fancy app.

00:20:01.430 --> 00:20:03.930
If they didn't
have the Fancy app,

00:20:03.930 --> 00:20:05.710
they would be taken
to the Play Store

00:20:05.710 --> 00:20:09.269
on Android, the App Store
on iOS, to install the app.

00:20:09.269 --> 00:20:11.310
So if you think about this
as if you were sharing

00:20:11.310 --> 00:20:14.122
an interactive post for
a high score on a game,

00:20:14.122 --> 00:20:16.330
the people who didn't have
the game when they clicked

00:20:16.330 --> 00:20:18.570
on that button would be
taken through a process

00:20:18.570 --> 00:20:20.740
to install the game
because somebody

00:20:20.740 --> 00:20:23.320
they know has recommended this.

00:20:23.320 --> 00:20:26.630
So in this case, let's say
Larry and Sergey get that watch

00:20:26.630 --> 00:20:28.710
recommendation from
me because look,

00:20:28.710 --> 00:20:30.620
I wear two Smartband things.

00:20:30.620 --> 00:20:33.660
I must know about watches.

00:20:33.660 --> 00:20:35.320
Fancy actually has
an affiliate model,

00:20:35.320 --> 00:20:38.720
so if Larry and Sergey
bought 10 of these watches,

00:20:38.720 --> 00:20:41.280
I get a small percentage.

00:20:41.280 --> 00:20:43.830
It's unlikely to happen
because they'd probably

00:20:43.830 --> 00:20:46.850
just buy the watch company.

00:20:46.850 --> 00:20:48.670
I don't get a
percentage on that.

00:20:48.670 --> 00:20:50.590
But the point
about this is, what

00:20:50.590 --> 00:20:53.990
you have is a human who has
reached a particular place

00:20:53.990 --> 00:20:56.590
within an app or a game,
has found some content

00:20:56.590 --> 00:20:59.770
that they think will
resonate with their friends,

00:20:59.770 --> 00:21:02.240
and you've been able to
nudge them to share that,

00:21:02.240 --> 00:21:04.650
and then when those
friends see that message,

00:21:04.650 --> 00:21:06.180
they click on the button.

00:21:06.180 --> 00:21:08.520
They become an app
install for you.

00:21:08.520 --> 00:21:10.393
So it's not just hey,
here's a cool thing.

00:21:10.393 --> 00:21:11.976
It's here's a cool
thing and an action

00:21:11.976 --> 00:21:14.030
you can perform
that will cause you

00:21:14.030 --> 00:21:15.970
to install on iOS or Android.

00:21:19.050 --> 00:21:23.520
Point being, people don't really
respond very well to messages

00:21:23.520 --> 00:21:26.690
from machines, but they
respond very well to messages

00:21:26.690 --> 00:21:29.380
from actual people.

00:21:29.380 --> 00:21:31.760
My parents have nagged me
for 30-something years.

00:21:31.760 --> 00:21:33.740
It still works.

00:21:33.740 --> 00:21:37.380
Whereas in a few months,
I get trained very quickly

00:21:37.380 --> 00:21:40.520
to ignore notifications from
certain games, certain apps.

00:21:40.520 --> 00:21:43.070
The point being,
human communication--

00:21:43.070 --> 00:21:46.350
having people be the one
to drive the sharing,

00:21:46.350 --> 00:21:48.960
whether it's of a high
score of a particular level,

00:21:48.960 --> 00:21:52.230
or if it's a screen shot or
a video of a particular piece

00:21:52.230 --> 00:21:55.350
of a game, is very,
very powerful.

00:21:55.350 --> 00:21:57.950
Because there's a unified
Google experience,

00:21:57.950 --> 00:22:02.540
this spreads to wherever there
are people are using Google.

00:22:02.540 --> 00:22:05.540
And the final piece
is that little site

00:22:05.540 --> 00:22:07.540
called google.com
we talked about.

00:22:07.540 --> 00:22:10.992
Now, when I share a message
or a screen shot or a video

00:22:10.992 --> 00:22:16.210
or whatever through Google+ from
YouTube or within your game,

00:22:16.210 --> 00:22:18.310
I've shared to specific circles.

00:22:18.310 --> 00:22:22.740
When those people are doing
searches later on, if things

00:22:22.740 --> 00:22:25.660
they search for match
the post I made,

00:22:25.660 --> 00:22:30.420
even if it's a private post,
the Think or Search+ your world,

00:22:30.420 --> 00:22:32.970
as you can see there, that
personalized search feature we

00:22:32.970 --> 00:22:36.090
now have for users who are
signed in means that they will

00:22:36.090 --> 00:22:40.010
see that private
post right here.

00:22:40.010 --> 00:22:42.750
Remember earlier when I shared
that post about the Submariner

00:22:42.750 --> 00:22:44.690
Rolex watch, and
it had the phrase,

00:22:44.690 --> 00:22:46.650
if only I had a submarine?

00:22:46.650 --> 00:22:49.520
Here it is in web search.

00:22:49.520 --> 00:22:53.230
So the point driving the ad
is that users can discover you

00:22:53.230 --> 00:22:54.340
through the Play Store.

00:22:54.340 --> 00:22:56.670
They can also discover
you through web search.

00:22:56.670 --> 00:22:59.970
The content you and
your users share out

00:22:59.970 --> 00:23:03.630
from within your game, often the
YouTube videos of your games,

00:23:03.630 --> 00:23:06.520
can be discovered again
by those same users

00:23:06.520 --> 00:23:09.000
through general web search.

00:23:09.000 --> 00:23:12.020
And they click on that,
they end up in that post,

00:23:12.020 --> 00:23:14.670
there's that Call
to Action button.

00:23:14.670 --> 00:23:17.490
They click on that, they've
now installed your game.

00:23:17.490 --> 00:23:20.570
So you don't have
this trap where

00:23:20.570 --> 00:23:22.380
you have to get
all the conversions

00:23:22.380 --> 00:23:24.060
in the first few weeks.

00:23:24.060 --> 00:23:27.360
You have content that lives
out for-- well, in this case,

00:23:27.360 --> 00:23:30.030
37 minutes after
I made the post--

00:23:30.030 --> 00:23:34.030
but theoretically, your content
can live for months and months,

00:23:34.030 --> 00:23:36.650
and those people can still
be coming back into your game

00:23:36.650 --> 00:23:40.150
months after the initial
flurry of traffic.

00:23:40.150 --> 00:23:42.820
So there's a much
